------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Requirements                                                         -
------------------------------------------------------------------------

CPython version 2.6 or later (Not 3.x ready yet.)

mysql
    you can just use sqlite for testing, but for the real deal, use
    mysql (postgresql should also work)

IPython (used for analysis shell)

Python Packages:
argparse (if using python 2.6)
configobj
discover
mysqldb
sqlalchemy
yaml

scipy
matplotlib

------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Setup                                                                -
------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Before you bother running any simulations, I highly recommend that
you perform all the unit tests and integration tests:

./run_tests.sh -ui

    If they do not all pass, you should make sure that all required packages
are installed, then start hunting for the problem.  If you need help getting
the software to run, please check the project's Google Code site (especially
the wiki).

# XXX add discussion about database setup

    If you have found a portability issue or other bug, please submit a ticket
on the project's Google Code site.

